articles.description: Freshman point guard T.J. Starks scored 17 points and Texas A&M toppled No. 24 Kentucky 85-74 on Saturday night in a sold-out and raucous Reed Arena.
articles.headline: Starks has 17 points, Texas A&M beats No. 24 Kentucky 85-74

images.caption: With former Texas A&M quarterback Johnny Manziel courtside, the Aggies make easy work of the No. 24 Wildcats in an 85-74 win.
images.name: Texas A&M hands Kentucky third straight loss

articles.description: Mike Daum had 27 points and 14 rebounds and made all 11 of his foul shots to help South Dakota State beat Oral Roberts 85-75 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Daum leads South Dakota State over Oral Roberts 85-75

articles.description: Xavier Cooks scored 20 points, Josh Ferguson scored 13 with 11 rebounds and Winthrop beat High Point 82-70 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Winthrop controls High Point from the start with 82-70 win

articles.description: Jordan Goodwin scored a career-high 28 points to lead Saint Louis to a 70-62 victory over La Salle on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Saint Louis holds off La Salle's late rally, wins 70-62

articles.description: Nick Dixon and Lesley Varner Jr. scored 14 apiece and Moe McDonald grabbed an offensive rebound and scored with a second left to send UT Rio Grande Valley to a 68-66 victory over CSU Bakersfield on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Moe's last-second putback seals win for UT Rio Grande Valley
